page.title: 12NATURE CONSERVATION
page.content: {Dollis Nature Reserve} {MIDDLE LEVEL Here there are alot of brambles,Dog Rose and sapplings. {LOW LEVEL There are two different types of nettle-the White and the Dead nettle. Also,Meadow Fescue,Vetch,Timothy grass,clover,Pink Campion and Buttercup are here. {WILD LIFE} There is also an overshadowed pond which is covered by a scum.This stops oxygen from getting through so animals are scarcely seen.But under logs you will find earwigs and wood lice. Mill Hill County High School have set up Long Worth Mammal Traps.We are hoping to erect a hide on an overlooking mound of earth. Recently someone has seen a fox and several kestrels have been spotted.
